  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      We do not know why diabetic patients cannot protect themselves against low blood sugar.
      Therefore, in this study, we will perform a comprehensive assessment of the body's response
      to low blood sugar by measuring changes in blood hormones, blood sugar production, and nerve
      signals.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Morning and afternoon hypoglycemic episodes of 70, 60, or 50 mg/dl produce increased blunting
      of subsequent counterregulation dependent upon the depth of preceding hypoglycemia. We wanted
      to test this hypothesis in healthy African American individuals to determine if there is a
      difference in their responses to varying depths of hypoglycemia.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
